@lucky13
I have had my fancy alphanumeric Medicare ID compromised and used for fake billings.  Despite numerous mail and phone reports to the Fraud Hotline, it took more than a year for Medicare to issue me a new card/#.  The only way the scammers could have gotten my ID (which enabled them to bill for fake DME supplies) was if someone in a medical setting sold them the information...  
A couple of offices do ask for the SSN because their systems still use it; I always go ahead, but with a verbal protest.

